# TypeScript Standards

## Strict mode

- `strict: true` everywhere; no `any` without justification
- Prefer `interface` for object shapes; `type` for unions/intersections
- Export types from `packages/shared-types`; avoid duplicate DTO definitions

## moduleResolution by package

| Location | `moduleResolution` | Import extensions |
|----------|-------------------|-------------------|
| `apps/*` | `bundler` (from base) | **No** `.js` suffix |
| `packages/ui` | `bundler` | **No** `.js` suffix |
| `packages/api` | `NodeNext` (local override) | **Required** `.js` suffix |
| `packages/shared-types` | `NodeNext` | **Required** `.js` suffix |

```typescript
// ✅ apps/h5, apps/web, packages/ui
import { Button } from "@ryx/ui/components/ui/button";

// ✅ packages/api only
import { ApiError } from "./errors.js";
```

Never add `.js` extensions in app or UI code — Vite will fail to resolve them.

## Naming

| Kind | Convention | Example |
|------|------------|---------|
| Components | PascalCase | `HomePage`, `WebShell` |
| Hooks | camelCase, `use` prefix | `useAuth` |
| API factories | `create*Api` | `createAuthApi` |
| Constants | `as const` objects | `BREAKPOINTS`, `SITE` |
| Source files | kebab-case or match export | `site.ts`, `HomePage.tsx` |
| Test files | colocated `*.test.ts` | `client.test.ts` next to `client.ts` |

## Imports

```typescript
// Order: external → workspace → alias → relative
import { useState } from "react";
import { Button } from "@ryx/ui/components/ui/button";
import { getApi } from "@/lib/api";
import { BREAKPOINTS } from "@/config/site";
```

## Env vars

- Read `import.meta.env.VITE_*` only in `apps/*/src/lib/env.ts`
- Extend `ImportMetaEnv` in `src/vite-env.d.ts` when adding vars
- Never commit `.env`; update `.env.example`
